content.description: Start matched in the seam and bump to the first disc hold. Continue to the second disc and exit right near a vertical crack. Climb it barefoot in sunglasses for the V3 grade and full value. With shoes its probably V2.
content.location: The problem is located below the museum of contemporary art on the sea cliffs. Best identified by the two "UFO" disc holds. This problem is North of the classic diving board problem.

content.description: 1inch Finger crack. Ring locks all the way up. Overhung last two feet.
content.location: North of trump wall hand crack by five feet. South of Scripps pier at La Jolla shores

content.description: Created by Concrete sea walls. 10 foot flaring hand crack. Last two feet overhung
content.location: From last Jolla shores parking area walk south towards Blacks Beach. Once you walk under Scripps pier look at wall to find gaps in the concrete sea wall. Crack is about 200 yards past pier.

content.description: Slightly flared 10-12 foot hand crack . Top 2 feet overhung. Created by a concrete sea wall
content.location: La Jolla shores California. Walk south from Scripps pier. Gap in sea wall provides a hand crack

content.description: Start on the lower disk hold at shoulder level. Heel hook with the right foot on to the disk as well. Then work your way up the the horizontal cracks to the top out higher disk hold.

A moderate and sustained beachside route in urban La Jolla, perfect for doing an ARC workout at sunset. Crux may be at the beginnings and end where the climb is more concrete and less stone.

Make this a tad spicier by removing manmade features like cement and drain pipes. Some of the footholds are quite glassy.
content.location: Route is on the beach in front of the Museum of Contemporary Art San Diego (700 Prospect Street, La Jolla). Street parking is located about 4 feet from this traverse, park and start climbing.

content.description: Start with your right hand on the crack and left hand on the lip on your left side. Start with your right foot on the slightly elevated portion of the boulder at the bottom. Top is at the ledge just above the crack.
content.location: Just north of Diving Board Direct and UFO Flow, but still in the same section of the beach.

content.description: Start matched on seam and dyno to the diving board like feature. From here finish the problem with the most classic mantle in La Jolla. A must do.
content.location: Casas. Underneath peoples wall amongst sand stone cliffs.

climbs.name: Are You Feeling It Mr Cracks
